---
// The Undergrowth — homelab & self-built tooling showcase
// Frond (Bramble homelab dashboard) + Trellis API
---

<section id="undergrowth">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="section-label">The Undergrowth</p>
    <h2>What runs beneath</h2>
    <p class="under-intro">
      The production work is visible. Here's what I've built to support it.
    </p>

    <div class="under-grid">

      <div class="card under-card">
        <div class="under-icon">⚙️</div>
        <div>
          <h3>Trellis API</h3>
          <span class="pill sage">Self-hosted</span>
          <p>
            A FastAPI backend running on my homelab, connected to a Neon Postgres
            database in the cloud. Manages bracket and match data via Challonge integration
            and exposes live JSON endpoints for vMix data sources. The platform LIANA runs on.
          </p>
          <ul class="under-stack">
            <li><span class="pill">FastAPI</span></li>
            <li><span class="pill">Neon Postgres</span></li>
            <li><span class="pill">Challonge API</span></li>
            <li><span class="pill">vMix Data Sources</span></li>
          </ul>
          <a href="https://trellis.vermilionrose.me" class="under-link" target="_blank" rel="noopener">trellis.vermilionrose.me &rarr;</a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="card under-card">
        <div class="under-icon">📡</div>
        <div>
          <h3>LIANA</h3>
          <span class="pill sage">Self-hosted</span>
          <p>
            A multi-tenant broadcast data CMS running on Trellis. Replaces Google Sheets
            as the source of truth for live show graphics: rosters, schedules, brackets,
            head-to-heads, and talent predictions, all editable through a web UI and piped
            directly into vMix as live data sources. First tenant: CBLOL UE.
          </p>
          <ul class="under-stack">
            <li><span class="pill">Multi-tenant CMS</span></li>
            <li><span class="pill">vMix Data Sources</span></li>
            <li><span class="pill">GT Title Designer</span></li>
            <li><span class="pill">Live Graphics</span></li>
          </ul>
          <a href="https://trellis.vermilionrose.me/liana/ui/" class="under-link" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Try the demo &rarr;</a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="card under-card">
        <div class="under-icon">🎛</div>
        <div>
          <h3>Broadcast Production Toolkit</h3>
          <span class="pill sage">Self-hosted</span>
          <p>
            A set of self-hosted production tools built to harden the show-night layer:
            validation that catches silent failures before air, telemetry that surfaces
            incidents as they happen, logs that survive past the truck. Each runs locally
            with no framework dependencies, no CDN, no build pipeline &mdash; built for
            show-day resilience over developer convenience.
          </p>
          <ul class="under-tools">
            <li>
              <strong>XYLIX</strong> &mdash; real-time stream-health dashboard: bitrate
              trends, dropped-frame alerts, encoder state, and a timestamped incident
              log on one screen.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>EiC Check</strong> &mdash; pre-broadcast go/no-go validator.
              Checks vMix state, integration endpoints, and dependency services in
              parallel, surfacing what's missing before air rather than during.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Show Event Log</strong> &mdash; production log for show night.
              Timestamped, category-tagged entries (segments, graphics calls, replays,
              incidents) that become the post-show debrief source of truth.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>GT Binding Validator</strong> &mdash; catches silent graphic-template
              binding failures before air. Cross-references vMix GT field names against
              the live data feed and flags mismatches the operator can fix.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Event show-day rundowns</strong> &mdash; per-show observer trackers,
              draft boards, and bracket/scoring tools built to fit each event's format.
              Shipped instances: CoD pick/ban, LoL rundown + draft, 2XKO rundown with
              bracket and live game/round scoring.
            </li>
          </ul>
          <ul class="under-stack">
            <li><span class="pill">Python</span></li>
            <li><span class="pill">Vanilla JS</span></li>
            <li><span class="pill">vMix HTTP API</span></li>
            <li><span class="pill">Chart.js</span></li>
            <li><span class="pill">psutil</span></li>
            <li><span class="pill">localStorage</span></li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="card under-card">
        <div class="under-icon">🌿</div>
        <div>
          <h3>Bramble Homelab</h3>
          <span class="pill sage">Self-hosted</span>
          <p>
            A personal homelab running on a low-power mini PC cluster &mdash;
            Proxmox hypervisor, TrueNAS NAS, Home Assistant, and Frond: a
            custom Homepage dashboard styled with the Bramble palette.
            Everything is botany-named, Tailscale-connected, and documented.
          </p>
          <ul class="under-stack">
            <li><span class="pill">Proxmox VE</span></li>
            <li><span class="pill">TrueNAS Scale</span></li>
            <li><span class="pill">Home Assistant</span></li>
            <li><span class="pill">Tailscale</span></li>
            <li><span class="pill">Docker</span></li>
          </ul>
          <img src="/images/bramble_screenshot.jpg" alt="Frond, Bramble homelab dashboard" class="bramble-screenshot" />
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  h2 { margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }

  .under-intro {
    color: var(--text-muted);
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
  }

  .under-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(340px, 1fr));
    gap: 1.25rem;
  }

  .under-card {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0;
  }

  .under-icon {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  h3 { margin-bottom: 0.4rem; }
  .pill.sage { margin-bottom: 0.75rem; display: inline-block; }

  .under-card p {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    max-width: none;
  }

  .under-stack {
    list-style: none;
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 0.4rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .bramble-screenshot {
    width: 100%;
    border-radius: var(--radius);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    display: block;
    margin-top: 0.5rem;
  }

  .under-link {
    display: inline-block;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--rose);
    text-decoration: none;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rose);
    padding-bottom: 1px;
    margin-top: 0.25rem;
    transition: color 120ms ease, border-color 120ms ease;
  }
  .under-link:hover, .under-link:focus {
    color: var(--blush);
    border-bottom-color: var(--blush);
  }

  .under-tools {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0 0 1rem 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.5rem;
  }
  .under-tools li {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    line-height: 1.55;
    max-width: none;
  }
  .under-tools li strong {
    color: var(--blush);
    font-weight: 600;
    margin-right: 0.25rem;
  }
</style>
